CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 14, reads: "At Four Corners Tavern - This group of celebrants is having a gay time at the famous Four Corner Tavern in Homestead. The popular spot is rapidly becoming a mecca for those seeking fun and relaxation at a surprisingly low cost.  Next time you are a member of a party that would like to see something new on the Pittsburgh scene, it would do you worlds of good to drop in on the Four Corners Tavern.  You'll probably meet old friends you haven't seen for years. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, and women, including one on right wearing arrow shaped brooch, gathered around tables in Four Corners Tavern, Homestead
